User experience is how a person, the user, feels about interacting with or experiencing a product.

for user to have good experience the product need to be usable, Equitable, Enjoyable, Useful. 
Usable: means making something easier to use means the design, structure and purpose of the product are clear to everyone.
for example: think about a ketchup, historically, kecthup came in a glass bottle the user had to hit the bottom of the glass to make ketchup come out. often, no ketchup or too much ketchup would come out of the bottle.
today, the ketchup bottle has been redesigned into a plastic squeezable bottle which make it easier to use and allows users to control how much ketchhup comes out.
